Molecular Simulation and Photonics]]></trackName><trackType><![CDATA[regular]]></trackType></track></programCurriculum><programDescriptions><contentLink><contentSummary xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[There is a wide range of opportunities at the Universiteit van Amsterdam; you can for example combine chemistry with biology or you can extend your knowledge of physical or more theoretical aspects of chemistry.]]></contentSummary><contentType>website</contentType><subject>objectives</subject><webLink xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[http://studieadres.nl]]></webLink></contentLink><contentLink><contentSummary xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[There are 5 specializations: Analytical Sciences; Biomolecular Sciences; Environmental Sciences; Molecular Design, Synthesis and Catalysis; Physical Sciences.]]></contentSummary><contentType>website</contentType><subject>curriculum</subject><webLink xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[http://studieadres.nl]]></webLink></contentLink><contentLink><contentSummary xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[Lectures, research, seminars.]]></contentSummary><contentType>website</contentType><subject>instruction modes</subject><webLink xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[http://studieadres.nl]]></webLink></contentLink><contentLink><contentSummary xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[Tuition fees are adjusted annually, for up to date information please see www.uva.nl/isp]]></contentSummary><contentType>website</contentType><subject>tuition fee</subject><webLink xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[http://studieadres.nl]]></webLink></contentLink><programDescription xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[Traditionally, organic and analytical chemistry lie at the heart of the discipline. As a multifaceted science, chemistry is a study in which every student can find an area suited to their individual talents and ambitions.

The Master's programme in Chemistry is a two-year programme taught in English. It is possible, for example, to devise a programme combining chemistry with biology or to focus on its physical or theoretical aspects.

The programme comprises five tracks:

Analytical Sciences 
Environmental Sciences 
Biomolecular Sciences
Molecular Design, Synthesis and Catalysis 
Physical Sciences

The Master's programme in Chemistry has been accreditated with the Euromaster label by the European Chemistry Thematics Network (ECTN). 

The University of Amsterdam (UvA) collaborates closely with the VU University Amsterdam the tracks in physics, chemistry and mathematics. Both universities have an excellent international reputation, with several research groups playing leading roles in various scientific fields. Their collaboration has resulted in a range of high-quality programmes. Students benefit from their expertise, existing networks and collaborative projects.
]]></programDescription><programName xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[Chemistry]]></programName><programName xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[Chemistry]]></programName><programSummary xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[The programme in Chemistry exposes students to frontline research. Chemistry has plays a key role in social and economic progress. It now forms the bridge between biology and physics & mathematics.]]></programSummary><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[beta]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[chemie]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[fysica]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[laboratorium]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[milieu]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[natuurkunde]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[natuur]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[scheikunde]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[wiskunde]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[exact sciences]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[chemistry]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[physics]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[laboratory]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[environment]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[physics]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[nature]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[chemistry]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[mathematics]]></searchword><webLink xml:lang="en">http://www.studeren.uva.nl/msc_chemistry</webLink></programDescriptions><programInternationalization><ErasmusMundusProgram>0</ErasmusMundusProgram><facilitationForeignScholarships>1</facilitationForeignScholarships><foreignStay>0</foreignStay><languageRequirement><languageExam>CAE</languageExam><minimumScore>B1</minimumScore></languageRequirement><languageRequirement><languageExam>CPE</languageExam><minimumScore>B1</minimumScore></languageRequirement><languageRequirement><languageExam>IELTS overal